author: Giorgio Mendoza
description: The NeoEyes NE301 by CamThink is described as a low-power edge AI camera built around STMicroelectronics’ STM32N6 microcontroller. The camera combines on-device neural network inference, a built-in web interface, and modular hardware design aimed at battery-powered and outdoor deployments. title: CamThink NeoEyes NE301 is an open-source STM32N6-based edge AI camera

author: Giorgio Mendoza
description: Crowd Supply recently featured LeafKVM, a compact wireless KVM-over-IP device that provides remote access to computers, servers, and HDMI video sources without requiring software on the target system. title: LeafKVM is a Rockchip-based self-contained KVM with touchscreen and browser access
